  <title>Intervals</title>
  <p>Before discussing scales it is useful to understand how intervals between notes are described.</p>

  <p>The musical distance between notes on  your instrument keyboard or on a musical staff is known as an interval. This interval might be described as a minor 2nd, a major 2nd, a minor 3rd, a major 3rd, a 5th, a 7th etc;</p>
  <p>The interval between two notes can be obtained by counting the number of semi-tones on the keyboard or staff but, when counting intervals, the first note, should be counted as one and not zero.</p>

